  <prompt>Update `spaarke-bff-dev` App Settings: `Redis__Enabled=true`, `Redis__InstanceName=spaarke:`, `ConnectionStrings__Redis=@Microsoft.KeyVault(VaultName={dev-kv};SecretName=Redis-ConnectionString)`, `Redis__AllowInMemoryFallback=false`. Do NOT restart yet (task 034 does verified restart).</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke operator; App Service config management.</role>
  <goal>`az webapp config appsettings list -g rg-spaarke-dev -n spaarke-bff-dev --query "[?contains(name, 'Redis')]"` returns the new values; KV reference syntax verified.</goal>
  <context><background>This is the cutover moment — App Settings now point at the new Redis via KV reference. Restart in task 034 surfaces verification log.</background><relevant-files><file>spaarke-bff-dev (Azure App Service)</file></relevant-files></context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">KV reference syntax.</constraint>
